primary_outcome.description:
Students will report their opinions towards 5 statements:
Children who use e-cigarettes are more likely to smoke cigarettes in the future;
Hazards of secondhand smoke of e-cigarettes and heated tobacco products are slight;
Nicotine content in heated tobacco products is lower than in the cigarettes, which is more difficult to get addicted;
There are a variety of carcinogens in the heated tobacco products;
Tobacco industries do everything they can to get young people to use tobacco products.
All the statements have 5 options from definitely no to definitely yes. The options will be recoded into 0-4 or 4-0, as appropriate, with higher scores indicating knowing more about the harms and misleading marketing strategies of ASPs.

secondary_outcome.description:
Students will report their opinions towards 5 statements:
Hazards of e-cigarettes are slight, can only cause minor health problems;
Reliable evidence shows that e-cigarettes can help quit smoking cigarettes;
Heated tobacco products contain tar, can cause a variety of cancers;
Heated tobacco products are harm reduction products, which is less harmful than cigarettes;
Tobacco industries conceal the harms of tobacco products for commercial gain.
All the statements have 5 options from definitely no to definitely yes. The options will be recoded into 0-4 or 4-0, as appropriate, with higher scores indicating knowing more about the harms and misleading marketing strategies of ASPs.
